{"type":"message","id":"650849f2","parentId":"6f06931a","timestamp":"2026-02-28T01:55:39.214Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call-c252f528-8ee3-4582-a395-2e2aa0b3a1d7","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The Egyptian Exchange - Today's Market Watch - Indices\nURL: https://www.egx.com.eg/en/indices.aspx\nText: This question is for testing whether you are a human visitor and to prevent automated spam submission.\nAudio is not supported in your browser.[] \n**What code is in the image?**\nsubmit\nYour support ID is: 2761761033435141725 .\n\nTitle: Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News\nURL: https://tradingeconomics.com/egypt/stock-market\nText: Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News | Trading Economics\n# Egypt Stock Market (EGX30)Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News\n* [Summary] \n* [Stats] \n* [Forecast] \n* [Alerts] \n## Egypt's main stock market index, the EGX 30, fell to 47786 points on January 28, 2026, losing 0.10% from the previous session. Over the past month, the index has climbed 14.51% and is up 59.86% compared to the same time last year, according to trading on a contract for difference (CFD) that tracks this benchmark index from Egypt.\n## Historically, the Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) reached an all time high of 256529.27 in December of 2023. Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - data, forecasts, historical chart - was last updated on January 30 of 2026.\n### The Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) is expected to trade at 45590.07 points by the end of this quarter, according to Trading Economics global macro models and analysts expectations. Looking forward, we estimate it to trade at 41885.78 in 12 months time.\n|Indexes|Price|||Day|Month|Year|Date|\n[EGX 30] |47,785.93||-48.62|-0.10%|14.51%|59.86%|Jan/28|\n|Related|Last|\n\nTitle: EGX 30 Historical Data (EGX30) - Investing.com\nURL: https://www.investing.com/indices/egx30-historical-data\nText: EGX 30 Historical Data (EGX30) - Investing.com\n[Investing.com - Financial Markets Worldwide] \nOpen in App\n#### Popular Searches\n##### Please try another search\n[Get 50% Off] \n* Sign In\n* Free Sign Up\n* [English (UK)] \n* [English (India)] \n* [English (Canada)] \n* [English (Australia)] \n* [English (South Africa)] \n* [English (Philippines)] \n* [English (Nigeria)] \n* [Deutsch] \n* [Español (España)] \n* [Español (México)] \n* [Français] \n* [Italiano] \n* [Nederlands] \n* [Polski] \n* [Português (Portugal)] \n* [Português (Brasil)] \n* [Русский] \n* [Türkçe] \n* [‏العربية‏] \n* [Ελληνικά] \n* [Svenska] \n* [Suomi] \n* [עברית] \n* [日本語] \n* [한국어] \n* [简体中文] \n* [繁體中文] \n* [Bahasa Indonesia] \n* [Bahasa Melayu] \n* [ไทย] \n* [Tiếng Việt] \n* [हिंदी] \n[Get 50% Off] \n* Sign In\n* Free Sign Up\n⏱ProPicks AI: February's update is now available. See which stocks are in/out &gt;&gt;&gt;[**See top stocks**] \n# EGX 30 (EGX30)\nEgypt\nCurrency inEGP\nAdd to Watchlist\n48,978.48\n+1,372.20(+2.88%)\nClosed·07:16:59\nDay's Range\n47,623.39\n49,235.65\n52 wk Range\n29,040.92\n49,235.65\n## EGX 30 Historical Data\nExplore the complete EGX 30 historical data, offering d\n\nTitle: EGX30 ended Monday with 2.64% Inecrease in benchmark index\nURL: https://en.firstbankeg.com/12426\nText: EGX30 ended Monday with 2.64% Inecrease in benchmark index | FirstBank\n\n## Egyptian Stock Exchange EGX30 has ended Monday 23 February 2026 trading session with market capitalization o\n\n### FirstBank فرست بنك البنك الأول فيرست بنك\n\n## News\n\n12426\n\n/12426\n\n# EGX30 ended Monday with 2.64% Inecrease in benchmark index\n\nEgyptian Stock Exchange «EGX30» has ended Monday 23 February 2026 trading session with market capitalization of 3.324 trillion.\n\nThe main index EGX30 recorded an Increase at today’s closing session by 2.64% to reach 50.870 points.\n\nInvestors traded on 218 shares, 174 shares rose, 22 fell and 22 shares remained stable.\n\nHowever, the turnover reached 1.03 billion securities dealt in cash executed on 115.30 thousand transactions, bringing the total trading volume to 5.71 bn\n\n## Most Watched\n\n### 59 Gulf banks feature in the «First Bank» list of the Top 100 banks in the Arab world\n\n[1 Analysis] \n\n×\n\n## News\n\n## Rating Lists\n\n## Top Banker\n\n## Analysis\n\n## Fintech\n\n## Banks\n\n## Video\n\n## Infograph\n\n## Banking Services\n\n- [Home]\n\nTitle: Egypt: EGX shows positive performance on Monday\nAuthor: \nPublished Date: 2026-02-24T00:00:00.000Z\nURL: https://www.zawya.com/en/economy/north-africa/egypt-egx-shows-positive-performance-on-monday-bnubymuh\nText: Egypt: EGX shows positive performance on Monday\n\nGO\n\nAdvanced search\n\nSocial media\n\n[Home page] > [ECONOMY] > [North Africa] >Egypt: EGX shows positiv...\n\nRELATED TOPICS\n\n[EGYPT] [NORTH AFRICA] [EQUITIES] \n\n> PHOTO\n\nArab Finance: The Egyptian Exchange (EGX) ended Monday’s trading session in the green zone after the EGX30 index rose by 2.64% to 50,870.06 points.\n\nBoth the EGX33 Shariah index climbed by 2.18% to 5,329.6 points, and the EGX35-LV increased by 2.75% to 5,247.71 points.\n\nThe EGX70 index and the EGX70 index closed the session higher, by 2.13% at 12,693.12 points and by 2.34% at 17,816.26 points, respectively.\n\nEGX’s turnover hit EGP 5.595 billion through the trading of 1.077 billion shares over 115,297 transactions, while the market cap stood at EGP 3.324 trillion.\n\nRetail investors took over 67.24% of trading transactions, while institutions equaled 32.75%.\n\nEgyptians dominated 85.92%, while foreign and Arab investors accounted for 8.68% and 5.4%, respectively.\n\nForeign and Arab traders were net buyers w\n\nTitle: Bloomberg Highlights Strong Performance of Egypt's Stock ...\nURL: https://www.facebook.com/investgateofficial/posts/bloomberg-highlights-strong-performance-of-egypts-stock-exchangeegypts-benchmark/1500693938725587/\nText: Invest-Gate - Bloomberg Highlights Strong Performance of...\nFacebook\n[\nLog in\n] \n## Invest-Gate&#x27;s post\n[\n] \n### [**Invest-Gate**] \n[18 February at 07:05] · Shared with Public\nBloomberg Highlights Strong Performance of Egypt’s Stock Exchange.\nEgypt’s benchmark index on the Egyptian Exchange delivered a 50% return in US dollar terms in 2025, driven by reform momentum and improving macro stability. Foreign investor participation climbed to 14% of total trading in February 2026, supported by renewed confidence and a recent interest rate cut.\nStrong gains were recorded across key sectors, particularly banking and real estate. Leading developers including Talaat Moustafa Group, SODIC, Palm Hills Developments, and Orascom Development Egypt were among the listed companies reporting solid profit growth.\n@bloomberg\n@egyptianexchange\\_egx\n[#Egypt] [#EGX] [#EgyptianExchange] [#Bloomberg] [#EmergingMarkets] RealEstate BankingSector ForeignInvestment EconomicReform CapitalMarkets\n[\n![May be an image of ‎text that \n\nTitle: Egyptian Exchange Closes on Broad Gains.. Benchmark EGX30 Surges 3.02% | Sada Elbalad\nAuthor: \nPublished Date: 2026-02-15T00:00:00.000Z\nURL: https://see.news/egyptian-exchange-closes-on-broad-gains-benchmark-egx30-surges-302\nText: Egyptian Exchange Closes on Broad Gains.. Benchmark EGX30 Surges 3.02% | Sada Elbalad\n\nSupervisor Elham AbolFateh\n\nEditor in Chief Mohamed Wadie\n\nsearch\n\n# Egyptian Exchange Closes on Broad Gains.. Benchmark EGX30 Surges 3.02%\n\nSun 15 Feb 2026 | 07:32 PM\n\n[Taarek Refaat] \n\nEgypt’s stock market ended Sunday’s session on a strong note, with all major indices posting gains amid robust trading activity and a clear tilt toward domestic buying.\n\nThe benchmark EGX30 index advanced 3.02%, closing at 52,015 points, marking one of its strongest single-session performances in recent weeks.\n\nThe broader market echoed the upward momentum, with the EGX70 index for small- and mid-cap stocks climbing 0.93% to 13,051 points. Meanwhile, the EGX100 index rose 1.54%, settling at 18,205 points.\n\nThe rally lifted the total market capitalization of listed shares to approximately EGP 3.38 trillion. Trading turnover reached EGP 8 billion, reflecting sustained liquidity and active participation across sectors.\n\nMarket se\n\nTitle: Egypt: EGX ends Wednesday’s trading session in red zone\nAuthor: \nPublished Date: 2026-02-26T00:00:00.000Z\nURL: https://www.zawya.com/en/economy/north-africa/egypt-egx-ends-wednesdays-trading-session-in-red-zone-au8p6xsf\nText: Egypt: EGX ends Wednesday’s trading session in red zone\n[] \n*\nGO\nAdvanced search\nSocial media\n[] [] [] [] \nMENA - ENGLISH\n* [MENA - ENGLISH] \n* [UAE - ENGLISH] \n* [KSA - ENGLISH] \n* [الشرْقُ الأوسَط] \n* [الإمارات] \n* [السعودية] \n[] [] [] [] \n[] \n* [Special Coverage] \n* [Abu Dhabi Focus] \n* [Corporate Earnings ] \n* [UAE Realty Market] \n* [The Future of Cryptos] \n* [AI: Shaping Digital Future] \nGO\nAdvanced search\n* [CAPITAL MARKETS] \n* [Equities] \n* [Bonds] \n* [Loans] \n* [ECONOMY] \n* [Global] \n* [GCC] \n* [Africa] \n* [Levant] \n* [North Africa] \n* [Policy] \n* [Islamic Economy] \n* [Islamic Finance Glossary] \n* [Islamic Reports] \n* [BUSINESS] \n* [Aviation] \n* [Banking &amp; Insurance] \n* [Commodities] \n* [Currencies] \n* [Digital Assets] \n* [Energy] \n* [Fintech] \n* [Healthcare] \n* [Investment] \n* [M&amp;A] \n* [Real Estate] \n* [Retail &amp; Consumer] \n* [SWF] \n* [Technology and Telecom] \n* [Transport and Logistics] \n* [Travel and Tourism] \n* [PROJECTS] \n* [BRI] \n* [Construction] \n* [Industry] \n* [Mining] \n* \n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772243739204}}
