{"type":"message","id":"4d8ab226","parentId":"08a2f74b","timestamp":"2026-02-28T01:55:51.495Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call-02d9d5bf-066b-47b1-ae7d-f78c134e9409","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: EGX Investment Roadmap 2026: Top Picks and Sectors - LinkedIn\nURL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/aymanelshahed_mubashertrade-annual-strategy-note-2026-activity-7416496246904930304-gbIn\nText: EGX Investment Roadmap 2026: Top Picks and Sectors | Ayman Elshahed, FMVA, MBA posted on the topic | LinkedIn\n\nAgree & Join LinkedIn\n\nBy clicking Continue to join or sign in, you agree to LinkedIn’s [User Agreement], [Privacy Policy], and [Cookie Policy].\n\n# EGX Investment Roadmap 2026: Top Picks and Sectors\n\nThis title was summarized by AI from the post below.\n\n[Ayman Elshahed, FMVA, MBA] \n\n1mo Edited\n\n- [Report this post] \n\nPleased to share a comprehensive roadmap for investing in the Egyptian Exchange (EGX), through the Annual Strategy Note 2026, titled \"A Year of Asset Classes in Tactical Rotation,\" from MubasherTrade Research (MTR). In collaboration with my esteemed colleagues in the research team at [Mubasher Trade Egypt] (c), we have covered the investment thesis for a range of vital sectors and industries, focusing on the underlying opportunities and potential risks. My contribution highlights 20 companies as liked stocks, providing a deep-dive analysis and investment thesis for 10 companies as top-pick stocks positioned for \n\nTitle: Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - Quote - Chart - Historical Data\nURL: https://tradingeconomics.com/egypt/stock-market\nText: Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News | Trading Economics\n# Egypt Stock Market (EGX30)Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News\n* [Summary] \n* [Stats] \n* [Forecast] \n* [Alerts] \n## Egypt's main stock market index, the EGX 30, fell to 47786 points on January 28, 2026, losing 0.10% from the previous session. Over the past month, the index has climbed 14.51% and is up 59.86% compared to the same time last year, according to trading on a contract for difference (CFD) that tracks this benchmark index from Egypt.\n## Historically, the Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) reached an all time high of 256529.27 in December of 2023. Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) - data, forecasts, historical chart - was last updated on January 30 of 2026.\n### The Egypt Stock Market (EGX30) is expected to trade at 45590.07 points by the end of this quarter, according to Trading Economics global macro models and analysts expectations. Looking forward, we estimate it to trade at 41885.78 in 12 months time.\n|Indexes|Price|||Day|Month|Year|Date|\n[EGX 30] |47,785.93||-48.62|-0.10%|14.51%|59.86%|Jan/28|\n|Related|Last|Previou\n\nTitle: EGX 30 Companies Stock List\nURL: https://www.investing.com/indices/egx30-components\nText: EGX 30 Companies Stock List - Investing.com\n[Investing.com - Financial Markets Worldwide] \nOpen in App\n#### Popular Searches\n##### Please try another search\n[💪 Find your edge in 2026 with 55% off InvestingPro] \n* Sign In\n* Free Sign Up\n* [English (UK)] \n* [English (India)] \n* [English (Canada)] \n* [English (Australia)] \n* [English (South Africa)] \n* [English (Philippines)] \n* [English (Nigeria)] \n* [Deutsch] \n* [Español (España)] \n* [Español (México)] \n* [Français] \n* [Italiano] \n* [Nederlands] \n* [Polski] \n* [Português (Portugal)] \n* [Português (Brasil)] \n* [Русский] \n* [Türkçe] \n* [‏العربية‏] \n* [Ελληνικά] \n* [Svenska] \n* [Suomi] \n* [עברית] \n* [日本語] \n* [한국어] \n* [简体中文] \n* [繁體中文] \n* [Bahasa Indonesia] \n* [Bahasa Melayu] \n* [ไทย] \n* [Tiếng Việt] \n* [हिंदी] \n[💪 Find your edge in 2026 with 55% off InvestingPro] \n* Sign In\n* Free Sign Up\n💹Will you get serious about investing in 2026? Take the first step with 55% off InvestingPro.[**Claim Offer**] \n# EGX 30 (EGX30)\nEgypt\nCurrency inEGP\nAdd to Watchlist\n41,987.11\n+443.65(+1.07%)\nDelayed Data·04:55:19\nDay's Range\n41,555.44\n42,014.43\n52 wk Range\n28,349.98\n42,624.11\n## EGX 30 Companies\nExp\n\nTitle: Egypt’s top 30 most valuable EGX stocks\nAuthor: Feyisayo Ajayi\nPublished Date: 2025-03-12T00:00:00.000Z\nURL: https://shore.africa/2025/03/12/top-30-most-valuable-stocks-on-the-egyptian-exchange/\nText: Notification [Show More] \n\n[Font Resizer **Aa**] \n\nReading:Top 30 most valuable stocks on the Egyptian Exchange\n\nShare\n\n[Font Resizer **Aa**] \n\nSearch\n\nHave an existing account? [Sign In] \n\nFollow US\n\nSHARE\n\n### **At a Glance**\n\n- The Egyptian Exchange (EGX) boasts a market capitalization of EGP 2.28 trillion, with its top 30 stocks accounting for 71.57%, reflecting Egypt’s economic stability and growth potential.\n- Leading sectors on EGX include banking, real estate, manufacturing, and consumer goods, driving liquidity, and economic diversification in one of Africa’s top financial markets.\n- CIB, Elswedy Electric, and TMG Holding lead Egypt’s most valuable stocks, underscoring strong investor confidence in banking, manufacturing, and real estate.\n\nThe Egyptian Exchange (EGX) stands as one of Africa’s oldest and most influential financial markets, with origins dating back to the 19th century.\n\nOver the decades, it has evolved into a well-regulated and dynamic marketplace, playing a crucial role in Egypt’s economic developmen\n\nTitle: Egyptian Exchange (EGX) - Listed Companies\nURL: https://www.african-markets.com/en/stock-markets/egx/listed-companies\nText: Egyptian Exchange (EGX) - Listed Companies - african markets\n* [Press] \n* [Advertise on AM] \n* [Our Partners] \n[**] [**] [**] [**] [**] \n \n[Log in] \n### Login\nUsername\nPasswordShow Password\nLog in\nRemember me\n* [Forgot Username?] \n* [Forgot Password?] \n[Subscribe] \n \n![] \n* [![]] \n* [![]] \n \n[![african markets] african markets] \n[![Research Hub Banner]] \n### Egyptian Exchange (EGX) - Listed Companies\nCompany|Sector|Price|1D|YTD|M.Cap|Date|\n[Abu Qir Fertilizers] |Basic Materials|65.66|-0.47%|+28.75%|82.85|05/02|\n[Abu Dhabi Islamic Bank Egypt] |Financials|39.00|-|+30.43%|46.8|05/02|\n[Acrow Misr] |Industrials|129.29|-|+6.09%|7.11|05/02|\n[Advanced Pharmaceutical Packaging Co.] |Industrials|2.33|-|-|0|05/02|\n[Ajwa For Food Industries Company Egypt] |Consumer Goods|116.04|-0.52%|-10.14%|2.33|05/02|\n[Al Baraka Bank Egypt] |Financials|17.92|+2.28%|+16.44%|13.03|05/02|\n[Al Fanar Contracting, Construction, Trade, Import And Export] |Industrials|3.17|-1.86%|-3.65%|0.05|06/01|\n[Al Moasher For Programming And Information Dissemination] |Technology|2.99|+1.01%|-2.29%|0.08|06/01|\n[Al Tawfeek Leasing Company - A.T.L\n\nTitle: Egyptian (CASE/EGX) Market Analysis & Valuation\nURL: https://simplywall.st/markets/eg\nText: Egyptian (CASE/EGX) Market Analysis &amp; Valuation - Updated Today\n[] \n[Investing Ideas] [Browse All Stocks] [Markets] \nHave your own idea? Try our[Stock Screener] \n🇪🇬 EG Market\n* [United States] \n* [Australia] \n* [United Kingdom] \n* [Canada] \n* [India] \n* [China] \n* [Argentina] \n* [Austria] \n* [Bahrain] \n* [Bangladesh] \n* [Belgium] \n* [Bermuda] \n* [Botswana] \n* [Brazil] \n* [Bulgaria] \n* [Chile] \n* [Colombia] \n* [Croatia] \n* [Cyprus] \n* [Czech Republic] \n* [Denmark] \n* [Egypt] \n* [Estonia] \n* [Finland] \n* [France] \n* [Germany] \n* [Ghana] \n* [Greece] \n* [Hong Kong] \n* [Hungary] \n* [Iceland] \n* [Indonesia] \n* [Ireland] \n* [Israel] \n* [Italy] \n* [Ivory Coast] \n* [Jamaica] \n* [Japan] \n* [Jordan] \n* [Kenya] \n* [Kuwait] \n* [Latvia] \n* [Lithuania] \n* [Luxembourg] \n* [Malawi] \n* [Malaysia] \n* [Malta] \n* [Mauritius] \n* [Mexico] \n* [Morocco] \n* [Namibia] \n* [Netherlands] \n* [New Zealand] \n* [Nigeria] \n* [Norway] \n* [Oman] \n* [Pakistan] \n* [Palestinian Authority] \n* [Peru] \n* [Philippines] \n* [Poland] \n* [Portugal] \n* [Qatar] \n* [Romania] \n* [Russia] \n* [Saudi Arabia] \n* [Serbia] \n* [Singapore] \n* [Slovakia] \n* [Slovenia] \n* [South Africa]\n\nTitle: Egyptian stocks post strongest early-year start since 2012 | AGBI\nURL: https://www.agbi.com/analysis/markets/2026/02/egyptian-stocks-post-strongest-early-year-start-since-2012/\nText: Egyptian stocks post strongest early-year start since 2012 | AGBI\n[Skip to content] \n[Skip to Search] \nFebruary 23, 2026\n* [About us] \n* [Partner with AGBI] \n[\n![AGBI] \n![Arabian Gulf Business Insight] \n] \n[Skip navigation] \n* Analysis\n* [\nMarkets ] \n# Egyptian stocks post strongest early-year start since 2012\nBy [Edmund Bower] \nFebruary 23, 2026, 9:19 AM\n* [] \n* [] \n* [] \n*\n![The EGX has been the second-best performing Middle Eastern market of size over the last 12 months, recording gains that reached 70 percent at the start of last week] Amr Abdallah Dalsh/Reuters\nThe EGX in Cairo has been the second-best-performing Middle Eastern market of size over the last 12 months, recording gains that reached 70% at the start of last week\n* Market cap surpasses $70bn\n* Capital inflows return after uncertainty\n* Rally reflects improved sentiment\nThe [Egyptian] stock exchange, which forms part of the MSCI emerging index, has produced its strongest start to a year since 2012 in dollar terms as capital inflows return after prolonged uncertainty.\nThe EGX30\n\nTitle: [PDF] Main Market Year to 03/02/2026 Statistics\nAuthor: \nURL: https://www.egx.com.eg/get_pdf.aspx?ID=54102&Lang=ENG\nText: This question is for testing whether you are a human visitor and to prevent automated spam submission.\nAudio is not supported in your browser.[] \n**What code is in the image?**\nsubmit\nYour support ID is: 2761761033474467037 .\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772243751491}}
